Doc Del. You're right. As burdensome to load as this spot is, let's keep it as is.  I think the passion would follow, but not completely, and I think the action, the momentum is here.  Thanks for the considerations, but kindly let me withdraw the idea.  Now then, let me roll up my shrink sleeves, been a long day in the land of haze, and read the new posts and the e mails (and thanks you all for both).<br>
JJ-The railroad-bumpersticker story touched me too. Surprisingly, and I'm glad for you.  Actually, once upon a decade I hated you all, hated you for not listening to me as the big mouth protestor who knew better.  Well..I don't hate you anymore, and even though my jungles were nothing, nothing, NOTHING in comparison with your experiences, I still feel kinship to you now...Not as shrink to shrinkee, doctor to patient, but as survivor to survivor. As one who learned lessons, and still has more to learn.<br><br>
Peace brothers, may your dreams be peaceful.<br>
